Forward and reverse primers for all genes were designed with USERoverhangs, to enable cloning into a pEAQ-USER compatible version of the pEAQ- 
HT
vector (Supplementary data, 
Table 1
) (
Luo et al., 2016
). pEAQ- 
HT
harbors the viral suppressor p19 and was kindly provided by George Lomonosonoff (John Innes Research Centre, Norwich, 
UK
) (
Peyret and Lomonossoff, 2013
). USER cloning was performed as previously depicted (
Nour-Eldin et al., 2006
).
